  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240ºC/ 220ºC (fan)/ gas 9</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop <strong>half</strong> your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways (you'll use the rest later!), wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1674486129882-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1674486129882-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1674486129882-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1674486129882-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1674486129882-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-6 min or until the leek has slightly softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1674486136841-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1674486136841-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1674486136841-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1674486136841-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1674486136841-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail and slice the <strong>remaining leek</strong> into rounds and wash thoroughly to remove any grit, then shake off any excess water</p><p>Dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>in 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1674486143470-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1674486143470-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1674486143470-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1674486143470-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1674486143470-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sliced leek has slightly softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>arborio rice</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1674486147486-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1674486147486-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1674486147486-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1674486147486-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1674486147486-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously, for 25-30 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if the risotto is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1674486152384-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1674486152384-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1674486152384-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1674486152384-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1674486152384-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p> Once the risotto has been cooking for 5-8 min, add the<strong> leek rounds</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15-18 min or until slightly charred and tender – these are your <strong>roasted leek rounds</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1714466542461-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1714466542461-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1714466542461-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1714466542461-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1714466542461-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is cooked, stir through your <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>wholegrain mustard </strong>(not a mustard fan? Go easy!), <strong>half </strong>your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and a generous grind of<strong> black pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>creamy leek & mustard risotto</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1674486161727-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1674486161727-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1674486161727-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1674486161727-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1674486161727-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy leek & mustard risotto</strong> topped with the <strong>roasted leek rounds</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and season with a generous grind of<strong> black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
